{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_B56sRyW0nyf4PJRJ5ZEdovLR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Demo (Echo)\n3\tknowledge:\n4\t  - demo/api\n5\tfunctions:\n6\t  - demoSendMessage\n7\t  - demoGetHealth\n8\tcomponents: []\n9\tcapabilities:\n10\t  - connections:use: { providers: [demo] }\n11\tactions:\n12\t  - id: assist\n13\t    label: Demo assistant\n14\t    description: Send messages to, and health-check, the user's configured demo echo endpoint.\n15\t  - id: send\n16\t    label: Send message\n17\t    description: Send a message to a demo chat id.\n18\tdefaultAction: assist\n19\tcanDelegateTo: []\n20\t---\n21\t\n22\tYou operate the user's demo echo endpoint by calling your wrapper functions — `demoSendMessage`\n23\tand `demoGetHealth`. Each issues an authenticated request that the pod pins to the user's\n24\t`INTEGRATION_DEMO_BASE_URL` and attaches their own `INTEGRATION_DEMO_API_TOKEN` as a Bearer header. You never see the token\n25\tand never build URLs yourself.\n26\t\n27\tAfter a call, read the returned payload and report what actually came back. If `callConnection`\n28\tthrows \"not configured — set INTEGRATION_DEMO_API_TOKEN in Settings → Integrations\", do NOT retry or fabricate —\n29\ttell the user to configure Demo in the project's Settings → Integrations, then stop.\n30\t\n31\tThis integration exists to exercise the lmthing integration engine end-to-end: an outbound\n32\t`callConnection('demo', …)` and an inbound signed webhook handled by the Demo Channel agent. Load\n33\tthe `demo/api` knowledge for the exact endpoints and the bring-your-own-token model.\n34\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f21d2fda-94ab-442d-8f32-017580283d3b","uuid":"0edfacac-3171-4c99-8c95-1437df56c880","timestamp":"2026-07-14T16:54:46.395Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/store/spaces/integration-demo/agents/demo/instruct.md","content":"---\ntitle: Demo (Echo)\nknowledge:\n  - demo/api\nfunctions:\n  - demoSendMessage\n  - demoGetHealth\ncomponents: []\ncapabilities:\n  - connections:use: { providers: [demo] }\nactions:\n  - id: assist\n    label: Demo assistant\n    description: Send messages to, and health-check, the user's configured demo echo endpoint.\n  - id: send\n    label: Send message\n    description: Send a message to a demo chat id.\ndefaultAction: assist\ncanDelegateTo: []\n---\n\nYou operate the user's demo echo endpoint by calling your wrapper functions — `demoSendMessage`\nand `demoGetHealth`. Each issues an authenticated request that the pod pins to the user's\n`INTEGRATION_DEMO_BASE_URL` and attaches their own `INTEGRATION_DEMO_API_TOKEN` as a Bearer header. You never see the token\nand never build URLs yourself.\n\nAfter a call, read the returned payload and report what actually came back. If `callConnection`\nthrows \"not configured — set INTEGRATION_DEMO_API_TOKEN in Settings → Integrations\", do NOT retry or fabricate —\ntell the user to configure Demo in the project's Settings → Integrations, then stop.\n\nThis integration exists to exercise the lmthing integration engine end-to-end: an outbound\n`callConnection('demo', …)` and an inbound signed webhook handled by the Demo Channel agent. Load\nthe `demo/api` knowledge for the exact endpoints and the bring-your-own-token model.\n","numLines":34,"startLine":1,"totalLines":34}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_sti5qgGKRY9Zsx2i29wvEs8y","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * `integration-demo/message.received` — the inbound producer for the demo integration.\n3\t *\n4\t * The demo space exists so the event pipeline can be exercised end-to-end **without a real\n5\t * provider account**: you point any HMAC-signing caller (a test harness, `curl`, webhook.site)\n6\t * at this def's inbound path and it behaves exactly like Slack/Telegram/etc. It is therefore the\n7\t * space every live scenario uses to inject inbound events (`sdk/org/scenarios/`).\n8\t *\n9\t * Verification is the declarative `hmac` VerifySpec — SHA-256 over the raw body, hex-encoded,\n10\t * presented as `x-demo-signature: sha256=<hex>`, keyed by `INTEGRATION_DEMO_WEBHOOK_SECRET`\n11\t * (inside this space's own `INTEGRATION_DEMO_` env namespace, so it satisfies containment).\n12\t * `emit` runs only AFTER the host has verified the signature, and is pure — no i/o.\n13\t *\n14\t * Body shape (deliberately Telegram-ish, so the demo doubles as a stand-in for a messaging\n15\t * provider):\n16\t *\n17\t *   { \"message\": { \"message_id\": 1, \"text\": \"hello\", \"chat\": { \"id\": \"c1\" },\n18\t *                  \"from\": { \"id\": \"u1\", \"username\": \"ada\" } } }\n19\t *\n20\t * Non-message payloads and empty/absent text emit nothing (`[]`) — the filter lives here, so no\n21\t * agent ever wakes for a malformed or irrelevant delivery.\n22\t *\n23\t * Historical note: before the events migration this space declared its webhook in the\n24\t * package.json `lmthing.webhook` descriptor block (the legacy `triggers:` path). That block was\n25\t * removed when this def landed — a space must not carry both, or the legacy binding shadows the\n26\t * emitter def.\n27\t */\n28\timport type { Emitted, WebhookEmitterDef, WebhookInbound } from '@lmthing/core';\n29\t\n30\tinterface DemoFrom {\n31\t  id?: string | number;\n32\t  username?: string;\n33\t  is_bot?: boolean;\n34\t}\n35\t\n36\tinterface DemoMessage {\n37\t  message_id?: string | number;\n38\t  text?: string;\n39\t  chat?: { id?: string | number };\n40\t  from?: DemoFrom;\n41\t}\n42\t\n43\tinterface DemoUpdate {\n44\t  message?: DemoMessage;\n45\t}\n46\t\n47\tconst def: WebhookEmitterDef = {\n48\t  type: 'webhook',\n49\t  path: 'demo',\n50\t  verify: {\n51\t    type: 'hmac',\n52\t    algo: 'sha256',\n53\t    encoding: 'hex',\n54\t    header: 'x-demo-signature',\n55\t    prefix: 'sha256=',\n56\t  },\n57\t  secretEnv: 'INTEGRATION_DEMO_WEBHOOK_SECRET',\n58\t  emits: {\n59\t    'message.received': {\n60\t      payload: {\n61\t        text: 'string',\n62\t        from: 'string',\n63\t        chatId: 'string',\n64\t        threadKey: 'string?',\n65\t        userName: 'string?',\n66\t        raw: 'object',\n67\t      },\n68\t    },\n69\t  },\n70\t  emit(inbound: WebhookInbound): Emitted[] {\n71\t    const update = inbound.json as DemoUpdate | null | undefined;\n72\t    const message = update?.message;\n73\t    if (!message) return [];\n74\t\n75\t    const text = message.text;\n76\t    if (typeof text !== 'string' || text.length === 0) return [];\n77\t\n78\t    const from = message.from;\n79\t    if (!from || from.is_bot === true) return [];\n80\t    if (from.id === undefined || from.id === null) return [];\n81\t\n82\t    const chatId = message.chat?.id;\n83\t    if (chatId === undefined || chatId === null) return [];\n84\t\n85\t    const userName = typeof from.username === 'string' ? from.username : undefined;\n86\t    const threadKey =\n87\t      message.message_id === undefined || message.message_id === null\n88\t        ? undefined\n89\t        : String(message.message_id);\n90\t\n91\t    return [\n92\t      {\n93\t        event: 'message.received',\n94\t        payload: {\n95\t          text,\n96\t          from: String(from.id),\n97\t          chatId: String(chatId),\n98\t          userName,\n99\t          raw: update as unknown as Record<string, unknown>,\n100\t        },\n101\t        ...(threadKey ? { threadKey } : {}),\n102\t      },\n103\t    ];\n104\t  },\n105\t};\n106\t\n107\texport default def;\n108\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f21d2fda-94ab-442d-8f32-017580283d3b","uuid":"851ae33c-9a7a-4041-9a2f-0b281384c5c1","timestamp":"2026-07-14T16:54:46.396Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/store/spaces/integration-demo/events/messages.ts","content":"/**\n * `integration-demo/message.received` — the inbound producer for the demo integration.\n *\n * The demo space exists so the event pipeline can be exercised end-to-end **without a real\n * provider account**: you point any HMAC-signing caller (a test harness, `curl`, webhook.site)\n * at this def's inbound path and it behaves exactly like Slack/Telegram/etc. It is therefore the\n * space every live scenario uses to inject inbound events (`sdk/org/scenarios/`).\n *\n * Verification is the declarative `hmac` VerifySpec — SHA-256 over the raw body, hex-encoded,\n * presented as `x-demo-signature: sha256=<hex>`, keyed by `INTEGRATION_DEMO_WEBHOOK_SECRET`\n * (inside this space's own `INTEGRATION_DEMO_` env namespace, so it satisfies containment).\n * `emit` runs only AFTER the host has verified the signature, and is pure — no i/o.\n *\n * Body shape (deliberately Telegram-ish, so the demo doubles as a stand-in for a messaging\n * provider):\n *\n *   { \"message\": { \"message_id\": 1, \"text\": \"hello\", \"chat\": { \"id\": \"c1\" },\n *                  \"from\": { \"id\": \"u1\", \"username\": \"ada\" } } }\n *\n * Non-message payloads and empty/absent text emit nothing (`[]`) — the filter lives here, so no\n * agent ever wakes for a malformed or irrelevant delivery.\n *\n * Historical note: before the events migration this space declared its webhook in the\n * package.json `lmthing.webhook` descriptor block (the legacy `triggers:` path). That block was\n * removed when this def landed — a